  "findings": [
    {
      "type": "security",
      "description": "The secret scanning regexes fail to match standard configuration formats:\n1. **Tier 1 JSON gap**: The pattern `(API_KEY|SECRET_KEY|SECRET|PASSWORD)\\s*[=:]` does not account for quotes around the key name. It will silently miss secrets in JSON files (e.g., `\"API_KEY\": \"...\"`) because the closing quote before the colon breaks the match.\n2. **Tier 2 Spacing/YAML gap**: The catch-all patterns (e.g., `API_KEY=.+`) hardcode the `=` operator without space tolerance and do not support colons. They will fail to catch spaced assignments (`API_KEY = value`), YAML (`API_KEY: value`), and JSON entirely, breaking the 'broad catch-all' intent."
    }
  ]
}
